{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17607918","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17607918"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:26:56+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:26:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15970"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15970","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15970"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0,0.54,0.46,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8661"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67279"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8661","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8661"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15970"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52731"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1845"},{"type":"tags","id":"3716"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"11061"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20737"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20739"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22525"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67279","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67279"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EPre-eclampsia is a pregnancy-specific hypertensive disorder that typically occurs after 20 weeks of gestation. It is characterised by new-onset hypertension and proteinuria.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most serious acute complication of pre-eclampsia?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Chronic hypertension","Gestational diabetes mellitus","HELLP syndrome","Placental abruption","Postpartum depression"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHELLP syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E is a severe complication of pre-eclampsia characterised by \u003Cstrong\u003Eh\u003C/strong\u003Eaemolysis, \u003Cstrong\u003Ee\u003C/strong\u003Elevated \u003Cstrong\u003El\u003C/strong\u003Eiver enzymes, and \u003Cstrong\u003El\u003C/strong\u003Eow \u003Cstrong\u003Ep\u003C/strong\u003Elatelet count. It occurs in approximately 0.5-0.9% of all pregnancies and in 10-20% of cases with severe pre-eclampsia. The condition can be life-threatening for both parent and fetus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options are less immediate threats:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGestational diabetes mellitus\u003C/strong\u003E is a separate condition and not a direct complication of pre-eclampsia\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPlacental abruption\u003C/strong\u003E, while serious, occurs less frequently than HELLP syndrome in pre-eclampsia\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChronic hypertension\u003C/strong\u003E may develop later but is not an acute complication\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPostpartum depression\u003C/strong\u003E is not directly related to the pathophysiology of pre-eclampsia\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHELLP syndrome requires immediate delivery regardless of gestational age due to its potential for rapid deterioration and maternal mortality.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Pre-eclampsia can progress to HELLP syndrome, characterised by haemolysis, elevated liver enzymes, and low platelets","Pre-eclampsia increases long-term cardiovascular and metabolic disease risk in the affected parent","Pre-eclampsia is a multi-system disorder primarily affecting the endothelium"],"references":["Fox R, Kitt J, Leeson P, Aye CYL, Lewandowski AJ. Preeclampsia: Risk Factors, Diagnosis, Management, and the Cardiovascular Impact on the Offspring. J Clin Med. 2019 Oct 4;8(10):1625. doi: 10.3390/jcm8101625. PMID: 31590294; PMCID: PMC6832549","Uzan J, Carbonnel M, Piconne O, Asmar R, Ayoubi JM. Pre-eclampsia: pathophysiology, diagnosis, and management. Vasc Health Risk Manag. 2011;7:467-74. doi: 10.2147/VHRM.S20181. Epub 2011 Jul 19. PMID: 21822394; PMCID: PMC3148420","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52731"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15970"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52731","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52731"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-04T15:20:05+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-04T15:21:04+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8661"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67279"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"23","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/23"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd30","name":"Obstetrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"create